# Context budget (advisory)

This rule is **advisory, not gating**. It exists to remind the steward/agent to consult the canonical context-budget bands before a BUILD-class pass, nothing more. It adds no checklist and no pass/fail gate.

**Canonical reference:** `docs/SOP/WORKFLOW_CONTEXT_AUDIT_001.md`.

## When to consult this rule

- Before issuing a BUILD packet (SELECTION → BUILD handoff).
- Before a retry in the same BUILD pass, if a prior attempt hit `retry_count > 0`.
- Before CLOSEOUT if the pass feels unusually heavy and you want to record the band.

Skip otherwise. This rule is not required for CLOSEOUT-only, SELECTION-only, or RECOVERY passes.

## Quick band check (see the audit doc for heuristics)

- **NORMAL** — governance overhead proportional to slice size. Proceed.
- **WATCH** — near ceiling. Prefer LOAD-ON-DEMAND SOP reads; trim the handoff packet; cap retries.
- **ESCALATE** — at/over ceiling. Split the slice, prune the ledger, defer a plane, run a CONTROL-PLANE interlude first, or stop and re-SELECT.

Full heuristics (canonical-doc reads, handoff-packet length, expected roundtrips, slice scope size, governance : diff ratio) and per-band advisory actions live in `docs/SOP/WORKFLOW_CONTEXT_AUDIT_001.md` §§3–4.

## What this rule is NOT

- Not a pass/fail gate on BUILD.
- Not a new enum in `docs/SOP/WORKFLOW_METRICS_V1.md`.
- Not an amendment to `CODEX_AUTONOMY_V1.md`, `JOB_REGISTRY_V1.md`, or `RELAY_RUNTIME_V0.md`.
- Not a replacement for `FRONTIER_STEWARD_PROTOCOL.md` "BUILD preflight gate" (that gate remains authoritative).
- Not always-on. Load this rule only when the checks above apply.

## Posture

Advisory. Steward judgment overrides the heuristic bands with a recorded reason. If a future audit (`docs/SOP/WORKFLOW_CONTEXT_AUDIT_002.md`, etc.) tightens or loosens the bands, this rule inherits automatically via the canonical reference above — no edit required here unless the reference path itself changes.
